{
  // ============================================================================
  // Worship Room — Verse-Finds-You Curated Verse Set (Spec 6.8)
  // ============================================================================
  //
  // CURATION RULES — every edit must respect these (Brief §2):
  //
  //   • Short passages only (target ~35 words; up to ~40 acceptable for
  //     foundational comfort verses like Isaiah 41:10 — the brief's "~"
  //     allows flex). Validation enforces ≤40.
  //   • No "prosperity" passages (no "God will give you the desires of your heart"
  //     surfaced as a promise).
  //   • No guilt/shame verses (no "oh ye of little faith" or mustard-seed-as-lecture).
  //   • No judgment verses outside explicit lament context.
  //   • Prefer Psalms, Lamentations, Isaiah, Gospels of John and Matthew, Romans 8,
  //     Philippians 4, 2 Corinthians — passages explicitly about God's presence in
  //     difficulty.
  //   • Every entry reviewed against the "pastor's wife test" before inclusion
  //     (would this verse, at this moment, land as grace or as judgment?).
  //   • Translation locked to WEB (World English Bible).
  //   • Version-controlled — changes go through spec review, not hotfixes.
  //   • "Fewer and safer beats more and dicey" — remove any verse you're unsure
  //     about, even if it means fewer than 180.
  //
  // Schema per entry:
  //   { "id": "kebab-case stable id (e.g. 'psalm-23-1' or 'romans-8-38-39')",
  //     "reference": "Display reference (e.g. 'Psalm 23:1')",
  //     "text": "Verse text (WEB, ≤40 words)",
  //     "translation": "WEB",
  //     "tags": ["one-or-more tags from known_tags below"],
  //     "excluded_contexts": ["zero or more tag names OR category names to suppress"],
  //     "approximate_length": <integer word count> }
  //
  // ============================================================================
  // CATEGORY → TAG MAPPING (Brief §"D-CategoryTagMapping" + Gate-G-NOT-HOPE)
  // ============================================================================
  //
  // The mapping below routes a post's category (the category the AUTHOR selected
  // when composing the post) to the set of verse tags the selection engine filters
  // against. Mapping uses Eric's pastoral tag vocabulary (see known_tags below).
  //
  // MENTAL-HEALTH AND GRIEF DELIBERATELY DO NOT MAP TO `hope`. This is not an
  // accidental omission — it is a load-bearing pastoral decision. Read this
  // BEFORE you "complete" either mapping by adding `hope`:
  //
  //   • For someone in acute depression, a hope-verse can land as a demand — "you
  //     should feel better, why don't you?" Hope-verses can be cruel in acute
  //     mental-health distress.
  //   • For someone in fresh grief, hope-verses arrive too soon. The pastoral
  //     work in grief is presence, not "look forward to better days." Lamentations 3,
  //     Psalm 88 — the Bible's own grief grammar — does not lead with hope.
  //   • The right tags for both are `comfort`, `lament`, `presence` — verses that
  //     ACKNOWLEDGE darkness rather than skip past it.
  //
  // If a future contributor decides hope-verses belong here after all, it should
  // come through a dedicated spec with explicit pastoral review — not a casual
  // "completeness" edit. The omission is the design.
  //
  // ============================================================================
  "category_tag_mapping": {
    "health":         ["comfort", "presence", "hope", "fear", "waiting", "endurance"],
    "mental-health":  ["comfort", "lament", "presence", "rest", "doubt", "fear", "loneliness", "uncertainty"],
    "family":         ["presence", "comfort", "endurance", "waiting"],
    "work":           ["endurance", "presence", "rest", "uncertainty"],
    "grief":          ["lament", "presence", "comfort", "loneliness", "waiting", "grief"],
    "gratitude":      ["gratitude", "hope", "presence"],
    "praise":         ["gratitude", "hope", "presence"],
    "relationships":  ["presence", "comfort", "endurance", "loneliness"],
    "other":          ["presence", "comfort", "hope"]
    // `discussion` is INTENTIONALLY ABSENT — Spec 6.8 Edge Case decision: posts
    // with category=discussion return `verse: null, reason: 'no_match'` rather
    // than receive a defensive default mapping. See plan Edge Cases & Decisions.
  },

  // ============================================================================
  // KNOWN TAGS (the enum the validation test asserts against)
  // ============================================================================
  // Union of CC's original 12-tag enum + Eric's pastoral vocabulary additions
  // (doubt, endurance, fear, gratitude, grief, loneliness, uncertainty, waiting).
  // Tags retained from CC's original (love, patience, strength, healing,
  // thanksgiving, praise, joy) for forward-compat — future curation may use them.
  "known_tags": [
    "comfort", "lament", "presence", "rest", "hope", "love", "patience",
    "strength", "healing", "thanksgiving", "praise", "joy",
    "doubt", "endurance", "fear", "gratitude", "grief", "loneliness",
    "uncertainty", "waiting"
  ],

